content.description:
Once upon a time, Hue Huge came to Crane Lake. He immediately locked his granite keys in his granite car. Luckily for Hue Huge, his friend knew a guy who worked on cars and was willing to help. Also, he had a machete. Hue Huge and this guy pried his door back just a bit, slid the machete in, pried it open a bit more, and were able to pop the lock. 

  The door, however, would never close all the way quite the same again and this crack was left behind for everyone to enjoy.
content.location: Up the Echo River from Nelson's Resort dock on the right side.

content.description: Climb the left side of a heart shaped rock upstream on Echo River as it feeds into Crane Lake. Once topped out, jump back in from one of a few height options.
content.location: Canoe, kayak, or motor boat up the Echo River from the Nelson's Resort dock. Rock is on the right 2-300 yards.

content.description:
Jug hold start and underwater foot. Move up to hand jam and crimp. High foot and big move to sloper shelf. Adjust feet, high left undercling, and a big step up to the finish.  

  You can jump back in the water from the midpoint finish, but beware: the water is about 6' deep under you before a rock shelf. Jump shallow, not deep.
content.location: Directly across the channel from the Nelson's Resort dock house.

content.description: Deep water bouldering options around Crane Lake.
